<task id="task_nvz_p3f_5x">
    <title>Vegan Breakfast Sandwich</title>
    <shortdesc>This quick &amp; easy recipe requires a stove, pan, spatula, measuring spoons, a
        knife and a toaster.</shortdesc>
    <taskbody>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>Ingredients you will need</cmd>
                <substeps>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>1 English muffin</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>2 tablespoons soy vegan sausage</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>3 thin slices of bell pepper</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>1 tablespoon vegan shredded cheese</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>1 teaspoon hot sauce</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>Â½ teaspoon vegan butter</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>1 tsp berry jam</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>pinch of black pepper</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>extra virgin olive oil</cmd>
                    </substep>
                </substeps>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Instructions</cmd>
                <substeps>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>Hand-press a patty out of the 2 tablespoons of vegan sausage.</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>Rub your patty in a light amount of extra virgin olive oil and place on
                            the cooking pan.</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>After about a minute or two on each side, remove your patty from the
                            pan and cover so it stays warm.</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>Add a small amount of extra virgin olive oil to the pan and cook your
                            sliced bell peppers on low heat.</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>While the peppers are cooking, toast your English muffin.</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>After the muffin is toasted, spread butter on each side.</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd> Once your peppers are ready, grab your patty and put it all
                            together.</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>Place sandwich on the pan open-faced and sprinkle cheese on top.</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>Close sandwich and cook on each side for one or two minutes over low
                            heat, pressing down lightly with your spatula.</cmd>
                    </substep>
                    <substep>
                        <cmd>Add hot sauce and pepper to taste, and enjoy your delicious vegan
                            breakfast sandwich!</cmd>
                    </substep>
                </substeps>
                <info>
                    <fig id="fig_qnt_g4l_5x">
                        <title>Yummy Vegan Breakfast Sandwich</title>
                        <image href="../../pics/sandwich.jpg" scale="50" id="image_es3_4vl_5x"/>
                    </fig>
                </info>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
